         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">29/9/65 ¶ Venerable and dearest friend. ¶  ¶ I despatch to day the 27th box of dry plants to Kew. It contains rather more than ⅓ ¶   ¶ of the Compositae, which Mr Bentham desires according to his last...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">65.09.29a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Directors' letters, vol LXXV, Australian and Pacific letters 1859-65, letter no. 197.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">29/9/65</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Venerable and dearest friend.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I despatch to day the 27th box of dry plants to Kew. It contains rather more than ⅓<seg style="font-size: 9pt; "> </seg>of the <name key="Compositae">Compositae</name>, which Mr Bentham desires according to his last letter to examine as material for his 3. volume.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">i.e. of Bentham (1863-78).</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> I was under the impression that the <name key="Myrtaceae">Myrtaceae</name> would together with several other calyciflorous orders cover the 3 volume; hence I did not send the <name key="Compositae">Compositae</name> before, though they were lying ready for nearly a year. The present consignment comprises 26 packages It is a real treasure &amp; [were]<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">were<seg style="font-style: italic; "> written over </seg>was <seg style="font-style: italic; ">or </seg>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">vice versa</seg>.</p>
               </note> the collection to get lost it could never be restored. Indeed I kept nothing back, except a few trifling plants, which I intend to diagnostify in my next <seg style="text-transform: uppercase; ">"</seg>Fragmenta”, thus 2 new Spilanthi, a new <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Eupatorium">Eupatorium</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> &amp; a few others.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">M described <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Spilanthes">Spilanthes</name> anactina</seg> and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. macroglossa</seg> in B65.10.04, p. 63; there were 27 additional Composites published in that fascicle of the <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg>, of which 25 were species of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Aster</seg>. No record of M ever having published a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Eupatorium">Eupatorium</name>
                     </seg> has been found (APNI, accessed 24 November 2020).</p>
               </note> I have now also <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Ageratum</hi>
               </seg> conyzoides from N.E. Australia.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In the box pr Kent I enclosed for the purposes of filling up vacant space a large specimen of <name key="Sarcophycus%20potatorum">Sarcophycus potatorum</name>.<seg style="font-weight: bold; "> </seg>Would you be so kind to see it sent to Dr Sonder when ever a consignment from Kew is to go to that Gentleman. He has particularly asked me to procure a plant with a view of enquiring further into the nature of its fructification.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>A report on my departmental work is submitted to Parliament.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B65.10.01.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">your regardful</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Could not a few roots of <name key="Crocus%20autumnalis">Crocus autumnalis</name> be sent to us? We have as yet not the plant in Australia.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Ageratum%20conyzoides">Ageratum conyzoides</name>
            </p>
